links.title: Trump's use of Regeneron's experimental coronavirus treatment creates 'very tough situation,' CEO says
links.description: President Donald Trump's use of Regeneron's experimental coronavirus treatment creates "a very tough situation" for the drugmaker since it hasn't been cleared for broader use, CEO Leonard Schleifer told CNBC on Monday. The president, who announced Friday that he and first lady Melania Trump tested positive for the coronavirus, was given an 8 gram dose of Regeneron's monoclonal antibody treatment, his doctors said.
